How long does fsck take? This operation will cut into fast/warm reboot time budget.

> How long does fsck take? This operation will cut into fast/warm reboot time budget.

I hope my reply to Qi Luo answers your questions.

If the filesystem has not been cleanly unmounted, fsck detects a dirty bit on the filesystem, which is a matter of reading a single block from the disk or the ssd. If clean, fsck then return immediately, . so the time budget is negligible. If the filesystem is detected as dirty, this might be a different story. But would-you want to mount R/W a filesystem which was not cleanly unmounted (power outage, kernel crash, etc.)?
@yxieca , i agree with @olivier-singla , it is better to do fsck during reboot. for fast reboot or warm reboot, we should umount disk cleanly before reboot.
